Filmmaker BB Sasore has collaborated with actress and TV presenter, Eku Edewor for a new film, ‘Breath of Life.’ The Nation gathered that the new film is the first feature in a slate deal between streaming platform Prime Video – Amazon Prime – Nemsia Films owned by Sasore and Derin Adeyokunnu. It was further gathered that the ‘Breath of Life,’ which is written and directed by BB Sasore is produced by Eku Edewor. Though the main characters of the upcoming film are yet to be revealed, Breath of Life tells an inspirational story about life and destiny where one must live to fulfill their purpose and cannot die until this is done.   Entertainers thrill on International Music Day in Lagos     Having great voice is a tip of iceberg, Raquel Hage     Sanwo-Olu eager to partner filmmakers to showcase Lagos,…   BB Sasore, whose Nemsia Films has produced ‘God Calling,’ ‘Before 30,’ and ‘Journey of an African Colony,’ is the famed writer and director of Nollywood hit film, Banana Island Ghost. It was further gathered two other films from the deal between Prime Video and Nemsia Films will be announced later this year. Nemsia films, co-founded by Derin Adeyokunnu and BB Sasore, has Adeyokunnu serving as managing partner and executive producer while Sasore serves as the creative director, writer, and director of most of their work. Speaking on the collaboration, Adeyokunnu said, “At Nemsia Films, it is our belief in ‘no gravity for the mind’ that has led us to work with Prime Video, one of the leading streaming services worldwide, capable of delivering our stories further than we ever imagined. We are tremendously excited about the collaboration and what the future holds for Nollywood.”